data.name: Collapse Piece
data.introduction:
A high-value currency circulating in small areas within contamination zones, produced by renowned individuals among the underground brokers. When minted, the issuing underground brokers often engrave their own logo on it. "Collapse pieces must be used with the corresponding underground broker—using the wrong one won't do!" 
Can be used to purchase designated supplies.

data.name: Sardis Gold
data.introduction:
Sardis Gold is a rare, precious metal widely circulated as a form of currency, valued highly from high ranking officials to civilians in contamination zones. "My New Year's wish is to be drowned in piles of Sardis Gold."
Can be used to purchase designated materials.

data.name: Exercise Badge
data.introduction:
The electronic badge pattern is well-designed, yet appears somewhat rigid and dull.
As proof of victory in a Combat Exercise, it can be used to redeem items in the Honor Hall.
data.description:
竞技场主干资源的货币
【不随着周期更换】

data.name: Module Slot
data.introduction: Backpack slots for module storage
data.description: 背包格数据，实际不是道具

data.name: Weapon Backpack Slot
data.introduction: Backpack slots for weapon storage
data.description: 背包格数据，实际不是道具

data.name: Intelligence Storage Module
data.introduction: Storage limit of Intelligence Puzzles

data.name: Async PVP Ticket Limit
data.introduction: Async PVP Ticket Limit

data.name: Access Key
data.introduction:
Only by entering the correct Access Keys can you obtain Intelligence Puzzles. While guessing right might yield some scraps, it's inefficient. It's better to purchase and use Access Keys.
Consuming an Access Key grants 60 Intelligence Puzzles.

data.name: Participation Voucher
data.introduction:
Special vouchers reissued by B.R.I.E.F., allowing lazy bounty hunters to go on vacation without worrying about missing rewards.
Can be used to participate in Tactical Evaluation.

data.name: Credit Token
data.introduction:
Electronic currency, independently issued and used by states under the control of the URNC, cannot be directly circulated. "I have to calculate the exchange rate every time I set off to another state. Can there be a Credit Token automatic exchange machine?!"
Can be used to purchase designated materials.

data.name: Credit Token
data.introduction:
Electronic currency, independently issued and used by states under the control of the URNC, cannot be directly circulated. "I have to calculate the exchange rate every time I set off to another state. Can there be a Credit Token automatic exchange machine?!"
Can be used to purchase designated materials.

data.name: Access Permission
data.introduction:
These are just a few simple codes, but when you use them to access the Sarr Database, you might find yourself experiencing unexpected surprises... Well, just manage the number of times you use it.
Can be used to access specific databases in Standard Procurement.

data.name: Segment Mark
data.introduction:
Electronic marks made and issued by B.R.I.E.F. are obtainable in the Boss Fight mode. Bounty hunters can passionately contribute their combat data in this way... It would be even better if they could exchange them for cute Dolls.
Can be used to exchange items in Battlelog Trading.

data.name: Withdrawal Receipt
data.introduction:
Some bounty hunters have protested the credentials obtained when accessing the Sarr Database, believing that the underground brokers are showing pity. However, more bounty hunters simply shrugged and accepted them. After all, having is better than not having.
It can be used to exchange items in Growth Stack.

data.name: Premium Gacha Coin
data.introduction: [Test Data] Obtained by purchasing or dismantling excess weapons.

data.name: Pickup Point
data.introduction:
You can obtain special points by handing items picked up during exploration to the manager. It wouldn't be an exaggeration to say it's the currency used in the contamination zone. "Hey, don't hand me all your junk. I buy usable materials, not garbage!"
It can be used to exchange items at the Manager Center.

data.name: Search Permissions
data.introduction: Special authorization granted by B.R.I.E.F. With it, bounty hunters can arrange flexible participation in "In-Depth Search" module operations according to their own needs. "I've done a lot of overtime today; I'll deal with the rest tomorrow." It can be used to participate in "In-Depth Search" module operations.
data.description:
人形经验本挑战次数-废弃
不是道具

data.name: Sync Permission
data.introduction: Special authorization granted by B.R.I.E.F. With it, bounty hunters can arrange flexible participation in "Standardizing Sync" module operations according to their own needs. "My favorite quote about money comes from Shakespeare's Timon of Athens. I am used to taking risks for gold." It can be used to participate in the "Standardizing Sync" module operations.
data.description:
金币本挑战次数-废弃
不是道具

data.name: Weapon Attachment Slot
data.introduction: Backpack slots for module storage
data.description: 背包格数据，实际不是道具

data.name: Combat Report
data.introduction:
A standard combat report, filled to the brim with pertinent information. "There's merit in giving them a read, but you'll end up dozing off more often than not."
Can be used to upgrade Dolls.

data.name: Standard Component
data.introduction: Standard parts obtained when dismantling weapons. These parts are in good condition and may have other uses.

data.name: High-Quality Component
data.introduction: Rare components obtained when dismantling weapons. These parts have less common specifications and are often used in more precise weapons.

data.name: Standard Gacha Currency
data.introduction: Used to draw on the general pool (can be considered as the previous Gachapon coin: Access Permission)

data.name: Access Permission
data.introduction:
These are just a few simple codes, but when you use them to access the Sarr Database, you might find yourself experiencing unexpected surprises... Well, just manage the number of times you use it.
Can be used to access specific databases in Standard Procurement.

data.name: Purchase Permission
data.introduction:
Although only a few simple lines of code are entered inside, when you use them to access the Sarr Database, a variety of weapons will appear... Control the number of times you use it. 
It can be used to purchase specific items during the Military Upgrade.

data.name: Practice Permission
data.introduction: A license issued by B.R.I.E.F. can be used to participate in the Overclocked Simulation.
data.description: 周常本B玩法的门票-废弃

data.name: Orderly Badge
data.introduction: An electronic badge is unique and distinctive in design. The pattern is based on the concept of ordered dispute, which shows considerable effort. Victory proof of Ordered Dispute can be used to exchange items in the Honor Hall.
data.description: 竞技场兑换兵械和地图货币2

data.name: Abyss Badge
data.introduction: An electronic badge with a unique and distinctive shape. The pattern is designed based on the concept of Breakout, and much effort seems to have been put into it. The proof of victory in Breakout can be used to exchange items in the Honor Hall.
data.description: 竞技场兑换兵械和地图货币2

data.name: Peak Value Summation
data.introduction: A virtual currency. If you want to get more, make a bold choice. It can be used to exchange items in the Jump Zone.

data.name: Talent Attachment Slot
data.introduction: Backpack slot for common keys
data.description: 背包格数据，实际不是道具

data.name: Daily Active Engagement
data.introduction:
B.R.I.E.F. provides progress points for completing Daily Quests. "If you don't complete quests, you won't have food to eat. At least it's a stable income."
It can be used to receive rewards from Daily Activity.
data.description: 每日任务的活跃度-不是道具-废弃

data.name: Battle Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they symbolize bounty hunters' combat strength and glory! "Isn't this like the points card you get when buying coffee?" They can be used to upgrade combat achievement levels and obtain rewards.
data.description: 成就原来的经验计数-废弃

data.name: Collect Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they are loved by bounty hunters who enjoy collecting various items! "People with a collecting habit would even want to collect this medal itself, right?" They can be used to increase the collection achievement level and obtain rewards.
data.description: 成就原来的经验计数-废弃

data.name: Service Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they symbolize bounty hunters' hard work and efforts! "I worked hard to train cute Dolls, not for this kind of thing!" It can be used to increase maintenance achievements and obtain rewards.
data.description: 成就原来的经验计数-废弃

data.name: Special Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they represent the serious attitude of bounty hunters towards work and life! "This... this can be exchanged for medals? Okay, thanks." It can be used to upgrade special achievements and obtain rewards.
data.description: 成就原来的经验计数-废弃

data.name: Drill Points
data.introduction: Every bounty hunter who participates in the Combat Exercise will not return empty-handed. Through battles in the Combat Exercise, they obtain supplies.

data.name: (Feature TBD) Weekly Engagement
data.introduction:
B.R.I.E.F. provides progress points for completing Daily Quests. "If you don't complete quests, you won't have food to eat. At least it's a stable income."
It can be used to receive rewards from Daily Activity.
data.description: 原每周任务活跃度-废弃

data.name: Silik
data.introduction: Originally, it was a commemorative coin with a specific meaning inside Elmo. It's hard to say whether the Commander had already foreseen the future when he named Silik. It can be used to exchange items in the Far Voyage Oasis.

data.name: Targeted Access Permission
data.introduction:
Just a few lines of simple code can help users access the limited-time submodules of the Sarr Database. Go ahead, there is everything you desire...! Do it according to your ability. 
It can be used to access specific databases for limited-time procurements.

data.name: Honor Badge
data.introduction: An electronic badge, although with complex patterns, still does not leave a deep impression. The victory certificate within Combat Exercise can be used to exchange items in the Honor Hall, and it will be cleared after the monthly settlement.
data.description:
竞技场兑换兵械和地图货币
【随着月度更新货币】现在欠缺后续的货币

data.name: Redundant Piece
data.introduction: Converted from unused Neural Archives, they can be exchanged for something else. After all, waste is not a good habit. It can be used to exchange items in the Neural Integration module.
data.description: 人形满碎片的转化道具

data.name: Paint
data.introduction: A spray paint can with fancy packaging. "I like that skin better; change it for me!"

data.name: Maximum High-Level Arena Tickets
data.introduction: Maximum High-Level Arena Tickets

data.name: Intelligence Puzzle
data.introduction:
Having detailed environmental data is a requirement for survival in the contamination zones. After all, no one wants to be the unlucky one who is eaten by an Obshare.
Used for combat.

data.name: Exercise Entry Pass
data.introduction: The permission produced and issued by B.R.I.E.F. allows bounty hunters to arrange participation in exercise drills according to their needs. 'Don't make empty promises; we'll meet on the battlefield.' It can be used to participate in Combat Exercises.

data.name: Peppermints
data.introduction: "There are always more than 30 days in a month when I feel energetic and can do more", said the Commander with a mouth full of mints. After use, you can add one daily action opportunity in the Voyage Logs.

data.name: Joint Application Certificate
data.introduction: Please don't act on your own; cooperation and win-win strategies can make your journey smoother. After use, you can add one joint action opportunity in the Voyage Logs.

data.name: Map Pin
data.introduction: Pull out the old thumbtack, quietly stick it onto the new action location, and pretend nothing happened. Consume one to change daily actions. Consume three to change weekly actions.

data.name: Simulation Access Pass
data.introduction: The permission produced and issued by B.R.I.E.F. looks like a beautifully packaged invitation. 'So... how is this different from a Combat Exercise? Whatever, we fight, right?' It can be used to participate in Military Simulation.

data.name: New PvP Ticket (Pending Packaging)
data.introduction: Unknown

data.name: New PvP Exchange Shop Tokens
data.introduction: Unknown

data.name: Experience
data.introduction:
In the crisis-filled contaminated zones, rich experience is also proof of strength. "You are already a mature bounty hunter, so this kind of thing can be easily solved, right?" 
It can be obtained in many ways.

data.name: Monthly Crystal Contract
data.introduction: A stable contract, suitable for bounty hunters looking for short-term profits. The contract takes effect from the date of purchase and is valid for 1 month. During the validity period, you can obtain 90 Collapse Pieces and 1 Access Key daily.
data.description:
大月卡
宝箱样式【开发背景下的产物】

data.name: Monthly Incremental Contract
data.introduction:
A contract for sale, categorized as a network service. After use, the simulation data can be modified through some technical means. Bounty hunters who wish to improve their material acquisition efficiency can consider purchasing it.
The contract takes effect from the date of purchase and is valid for one month. During this time the yield for the first two runs of Standardizing Sync per day and the number of rewinds per day will be increased.

data.name: Battle Decoration
data.introduction: Awarded by B.R.I.E.F. to bounty hunters with outstanding accomplishments. This is a symbol of glory and also a precious memento that can be exchanged for special rewards from B.R.I.E.F.

data.name: Decoration Log
data.introduction: A record of a bounty hunter's glorious deeds with B.R.I.E.F. Each stroke of the pen in this log describes your great achievements.

data.name: Test timed item setup 1
data.introduction: According to legend, there is a copper pendant box that can dispel darkness. It is magical and beautiful. If the person who opens it has an extremely strong wish, they will be able to see the girl in a white dress living inside.

data.name: Test timed item setup 2
data.introduction: Legend has it that there is a flower that grows beneath the heart of a whale. Even in the ocean's darkest depths, this flower can emit a bright light. Wherever it illuminates, darkness will never return.

data.name: Test timed item setup 3
data.introduction: According to legend, every planet has its own unique core. When a planet falls into darkness, the Fairy of Enlightenment spins the core, returning the world to light. Unfortunately, this core appears to have been polluted.

data.name: Posture - Mayling
data.introduction: Even cuter lines will accompany Mayling's habitual, cute movements. Once obtained, you can unlock Mayling's special appearance and corresponding voice lines.
data.description: 用于指代美玲动作奖励

data.name: Mileage
data.introduction: "You can only accumulate mileage by driving effectively according to the plan. Doing nothing is just a waste of energy and idling in place." Mileage accumulated after completing actions along the way.

data.name: Reset Mileage
data.introduction: "You can only accumulate mileage by driving effectively according to the plan. Doing nothing is just a waste of energy and idling in place." Mileage accumulated after completing actions along the way.

data.name: Krolik
data.introduction: A Doll with a slightly irritable personality who has little interest in matters unrelated to her but possesses an impeccable sense of responsibility. Even task she loathes like "serving as Nemesis' exclusive translator," she completes them wholeheartedly.

data.name: Nemesis
data.introduction: A Doll keen on mysticism and divination, she carries a magical tool known as a 'prism.' She expresses divination results in a mysterious, puzzling language style. She remains a reliable companion - except for being challenging to communicate with.

data.name: Colphne
data.introduction: While she is usually an enthusiastic Doll, she occasionally shows a completely different, cold expression. What lays in the syringe that she holds? Is it to save, or to end a life?

data.name: Lenna
data.introduction: A cheerful and friendly Doll who goes to great lengths to protect her cherished family. Over time, she has become more composed and developed a perfect smile when interacting with others. She also "forcibly" gives her family heartfelt hugs whenever she sees them.

data.name: Vepley
data.introduction: An idol who shines on the unique stage, the "battlefield"! She prepares meticulously every day for her next performance—this way, she will not easily trip or bump into others again.

data.name: Groza
data.introduction: A mature and composed elite Doll, she is undeniably the squad's core. Despite the squad members' diverse personalities, she seamlessly unites their strengths. With her presence, nothing will become a problem.

data.name: Peritya
data.introduction: A laid-back and curious Doll. To her, combat, survival, and a spectrum of emotions are all part of this vast world. Compared to the digital realm, she finds countless undiscovered pleasures in this expansive reality. Hm... that cloud has finally covered the sun. Time to lie down and rest for a while.

data.name: Sharkry
data.introduction: A mischievous, impish Doll whose sweet smiles hide a cute cunning. She is hungry not only for the stage but also for the boundless adoration from her customers. ♥

data.name: Dushevnaya
data.introduction: A highly sensitive Doll who has lost her neural records, persistently searching for her past and wholeheartedly fulfilling the requests of others. The way she expresses her emotions can be both somewhat exaggerated and immature, often leaving others puzzled in her wake. In truth, these mannerisms are simply a way to mask her own awkwardness and insecurities.

data.name: Cheeta
data.introduction: This Doll with a ceaseless fountain of inspiration is Griffin's Queen of Inventions. Undeterred by countless setbacks, her mind churns out a whirlwind of quirky, headache-inducing ideas. Yet, when the moment demands it, she always manages to come up with ingenious solutions.

data.name: Tololo
data.introduction: A serene Doll who finds solace under the starry sky. Hidden beneath her reticence is a delicate and sensitive soul. When the world slumbers, she confides in the vast cosmos and delights in the stars that seem to shine just for her.

data.name: Nagant
data.introduction: A Doll who likes to play the mature grown-up but looks up to heroes and also aspires to be one. Even after leaving the battlefield, she continues to shine as a security Doll, ensuring peaceful nights.

data.name: Qiongjiu
data.introduction: A Doll who limits her personal freedom in order to shoulder her team's heavy responsibilities. She dedicates her time and energy to Griffin, but is capable of maintaining her individuality thanks to her precise and efficient work planning. She never deviates, and never breaks the rules; rather than changing the plan, she prefers to change reality and herself.

data.name: Centaureissi
data.introduction: A humble yet principled Doll. She brews aromatic coffee and stands as the steadfast guardian of the café—she is the irreplaceable shield of "Zucchero".

data.name: Sabrina
data.introduction: A Doll passionate about culinary research and enjoying food, the kitchen is her new battlefield. Loves sharing her cooking process, though aroma may have boundaries, her smile spreads through the network, infecting every viewer.

data.name: Daiyan
data.introduction: A gentle and reserved Doll who roams the lands with her guzheng and her bandmates from "Monsoon". When she plucks the strings, she evokes the deepest desires buried in the hearts of her listeners—listening to all, and embracing all.

data.name: Mosin-Nagant
data.introduction: A Doll who loves to help others and strives to improve her negative mindset. Her motto is to never avoid challenges; once motivated, she gives her all. While negative thoughts may linger in her neural cloud, her radiant smile and enthusiastic actions surely inspire many of her companions.

data.name: Makiatto
data.introduction: A calm, proud, yet awkward Doll who isn't good at expressing herself. She loves fluffy little animals and overly sweet macchiatos. Always a loner, her gaze often lingers somewhere. When will she finally get the response she's been longing for?

data.name: Jiangyu
data.introduction: A lively and enthusiastic Doll who follows in her older sister's footsteps with a carefree spirit. She roams the lands with her bandmates, bringing fresh and fiery notes to "Monsoon".

data.name: Ksenia
data.introduction: A Doll with an unusual obsession with making money, she finds a sense of security by working hard to earn it and then spending it all. However, the time she spends working with her reliable companions is equally her treasure.

data.name: Ullrid
data.introduction: A Doll with great ambitions. She draws friends to her side with her bold nature and strong decisiveness. However, she occasionally longs for a quiet corner to unload her burden and rest.

data.name: Littara
data.introduction: An extremely introverted doll who needs to communicate through writing. She is meticulous and thorough, playing a "strategist" role in the team. After switching to a new Imprint Model, she has become even more reliable, supporting her teammates' dreams daily.

data.name: Suomi
data.introduction: A cute, conscientious, and kind-hearted Doll who will do what it takes for a mission. She bravely steps forward for her companions in the Community whilst she wanders the lands in search of those she treasures dearly. You need not worry when entrusting her with assignments; she will never fail to meet your expectations or complete her missions.

data.name: Papasha
data.introduction: A warm-hearted Doll who doesn't know how to say "no", she has become a versatile helper through self-study in order to better handle any request. She is willing to give everything to protect everyone. When you encounter difficulties, feel free to rely on her—no matter what it is, Papasha will make it happen!

data.name: Lotta
data.introduction: This Doll, who is both exceedingly shy and cautious, has a knack for noticing subtle details that others miss. Do keep in mind that her slow and reserved nature when socializing may require some extra patience and understanding.

data.name: Andoris
data.introduction: A gentle, approachable Doll. Although she has performance limitations, she does not indulge in self pity, but instead proactively searches for a place she can call home. A Doll who embraces and accomodates everyone around her, she has become a source of refuge for others without realizing it.

data.name: Faye
data.introduction: A Doll whose appearance contrasts greatly with her personality. Small in stature yet imposing, she carries a gun on one hand and an axe in another, creating a presence that would scare off most people. However, if you are willing to look past her appearance and get to understand her better, you will find that, behind her intolerant expression and irritable tone lies a delicate, sensitive soul. She too, is awaiting your warmth.

data.name: Vector
data.introduction: A regularly pessimistic Doll. However, as the leader of H.I.D.E. 404's Team B, Vector will absolutely push through and endure till the very last moment with her teammates in the face of adversity, no matter how depressing the outcomes of her calculations.

data.name: Belka
data.introduction: Her innocence, liveliness and considerate personality is written on her face. Absolutely loyal to the Commander and her big sister, she is a Doll who strives to become an elite Doll loved by everyone. With her around, awkward silences are no longer a thing!

data.name: Springfield
data.introduction: Gentle, strong and understanding of others, she is a tactful and witty Doll who mingles well with different groups of people without allowing anyone to take advantage of her. Behind her tolerance lies an adherence to principles, that being Springfield's one and only principle— She shall always protect her friends and those who are important to her.

data.name: Qiuhua
data.introduction: A passionate, high-energy Doll with an optimistic outlook on life. As a gourmet hunter in the Yellow Zone, she's made it her mission to develop new ingredients to tackle food shortages. Standing against injustice is a way of life for her and her credo is to never let a conversation trail off. "While I can't say I approve of adding ketchup to deep fried pork, if that's how you like it, then I suppose I can live with it."

data.name: Zhaohui
data.introduction: A stoic Doll with rich combat experience, she is unpretentious and decisive in action. As the leader of Monsoon Squad, she excels in combat and handling team affairs but is still a novice at lightening the mood. Don't hesitate to welcome her—a hero pursuing justice is always worthy of trust.

data.name: Mechty
data.introduction: A Doll who approaches everything with peak laziness—except for gaming and reading manga. She's mastered the ultimate skill: falling asleep anytime, anywhere, under any circumstance. Although she seems to embody the philosophy of "lying flat" to the extreme, she reveals her dependable side in times of crisis—though in her words, "It'd be better if we just never ran into any 'crisis' at all…"

data.name: Klukai
data.introduction: Elegant and composed; a Doll brimming with confidence. She aspires to make every member of H.I.D.E. 404 into an elite. Only those who are familiar with her know the tenderness that lies behind her cold, strong-willed demeanor.

data.name: Peri
data.introduction: A cute little Doll with big dreams, Peri has grown into a strong, independent Doll while following in the footsteps of her master. Her cheerful and lively personality has won the trust of many clients while her wits and experience have allowed her to avoid many pitfalls. All her efforts are to become a super cool and reliable Doll, so why not try relying on her a little?

data.name: Yoohee
data.introduction: A passionate and responsible Doll who's devoted to the art of dancing. A compliment from the Commander set her on the path to becoming a dancer, and she founded the dancing troupe called "Sparkle Squad" to provide wandering Dolls with a place to call home and thus do justice to her position as a veteran Doll. She has never slacked off in her quest to perfect her art; diligence and willingness to learn are the cornerstones of her efforts while never giving up and keeping her eyes on the goals are the secret of her success. Don't question it, just trust her, because when she says she'll do it, she means it. "Keep up with the beat! Let's blow the roof off this place!"

data.name: Nikketa
data.introduction: A security officer who upholds justice, a kind older sister figure who cherishes children, a big spender who uses up all her monthly earnings— Who is to say that these three identities can't belong to the same person? Nikketa fights in the frontlines of justice, calmly demonstrating her values and beliefs. Yet when she faces you, another side of her emerges. "My work has taught me not to trust anyone. Boss is the exception though. We are fellow partners in the pursuit of justice."

data.name: Krolik Neural Archive

Krolik's Neural Archive, can be used for this Doll's Neural Fortification.

data.name: Alloy Custom Plier
data.introduction: A weapon blueprint for the mini machine gun that allows for a beautiful change in armament. "There is no pliers more useful than these." It can be used to make the mini machine gun.

data.name: Automatic Fire Control Module
data.introduction: A fire control module with a built-in laser rangefinder, micro ballistic computer, automatic Sight, and two-way stabilizer. "Using this, I feel that the fixed turret is more targeted in positioning when destroying the enemy." It can be used to develop fixed turrets.

data.name: High-Elasticity Composite Material
data.introduction: A new type of composite material characterized by high elasticity and high strength is suitable for refined modifications. "You can use it to make the most important parts confidently." It can be used to develop enemy-seeking missiles.

data.name: Detachable Machine Gun Unit
data.introduction: A disassemble-for-use, very convenient standard MG module. "If it breaks, you can disassemble it and take it for repair..." It can be used to develop a mobile machine gun vehicle.

data.name: High-Density Protective Case
data.introduction: A shipping box made of unique materials with high airtightness. "The best packaging box you can imagine". It can be used to develop maintenance kits.

data.name: Titanium Alloy Shockproof Case
data.introduction: A sturdy, shockproof, and drop-resistant transport box. "A practical alloy box of good quality". It can be used to develop short-acting burst components.

data.name: High-Entropy Alloy
data.introduction: It is an alloy that uses multiple main elements as basic components, usually containing more than 5 main elements. The atomic fraction of each main element is between 5% and 35%. The structure and properties are different from traditional alloys. It has excellent mechanical properties, friction and wear resistance, corrosion resistance, high temperature resistance, and other properties, which can meet the current upgrade needs of all types of weaponry. However, due to the difficult production process and rare output, it is challenging to obtain.

data.name: Data Drive
data.introduction:
A data storage disk containing various standard UAV operating modules. Even the most discerning bounty hunter would struggle to find its shortcomings.
This can be used for custom UAV configurations.

data.name: Daily Active Engagement
data.introduction:
B.R.I.E.F. provides progress points for completing Daily Quests. "If you don't complete quests, you won't have food to eat. At least it's a stable income."
It can be used to receive rewards from Daily Activity.

data.name: Battle Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they symbolize bounty hunters' combat strength and glory! "Isn't this like the points card you get when buying coffee?" They can be used to upgrade combat achievement levels and obtain rewards.

data.name: Collect Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they are loved by bounty hunters who enjoy collecting various items! "People with a collecting habit would even want to collect this medal itself, right?" They can be used to increase the collection achievement level and obtain rewards.

data.name: Service Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they symbolize bounty hunters' hard work and efforts! "I worked hard to train cute Dolls, not for this kind of thing!" It can be used to increase maintenance achievements and obtain rewards.

data.name: Special Badges
data.introduction: The electronic medals issued by B.R.I.E.F. may look ordinary, but they represent the serious attitude of bounty hunters towards work and life! "This... this can be exchanged for medals? Okay, thanks." It can be used to upgrade special achievements and obtain rewards.

data.name: Drill Points
data.introduction: Every bounty hunter who participates in the Combat Exercise will not return empty-handed. Through battles in the Combat Exercise, they obtain supplies.

data.name: (Feature TBD) Weekly Engagement
data.introduction:
B.R.I.E.F. provides progress points for completing Daily Quests. "If you don't complete quests, you won't have food to eat. At least it's a stable income."
It can be used to receive rewards from Daily Activity.

data.name: Handmade Lucky Knot
data.introduction:
The peace knot, made with thick red thread, contains the owner's good wishes for the future. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Hoop Earring
data.introduction:
The plain black hoop earring is in good condition despite having been worn by their owner for many years. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Silver Tie Pin
data.introduction:
A silver tie clip with a fleur-de-lis pattern on the front and "T&C" printed on the back. Even in the safety zones, this is a rare decoration. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Sealed Document Bag
data.introduction:
An ordinary-looking file bag containing a summary report of local exceptional electronic intrusion cases. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Smiling Goliath
data.introduction:
A casual sketch of Goliath. The artist gave Goliath a slightly naughty smile, making it look cute. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Nemertea Specimen Slide
data.introduction:
A slice of tissue specimen of the Boojum "Nemertea" emits a faint blue fluorescence in a darker environment. The battle required to obtain it is hard to imagine. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Tattered Access Pass
data.introduction:
A weathered hospital pass with scratches all over its surface. Now, only the last name of the former owner, "Monak", can be seen. Perhaps its owner has been through something. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Rough Bird Beak Mask
data.introduction:
A crudely crafted bird-beak mask modeled after the defense device commonly used by doctors in medieval Europe, and the person who made it seems to have put a lot of effort into it. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: A Box of Blocks
data.introduction:
A box of scattered wooden building blocks has been repeatedly assembled, pieced together, and then torn down and rebuilt until they are in the most perfect state. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Eutis
data.introduction:
A special drink in a glass bottle. It is rumored that it can temporarily relieve people from the pain caused by the Collapse Radiation. As for the truth of the rumor, who can be sure before drinking this suspicious liquid? 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Print Magazine
data.introduction:
A copy of "Caucasus Today" magazine. While printed media has long been in decline, for reasons unknown, this publication continues to be published.
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Unusual Snowflake Sample
data.introduction:
Snowflake samples stored in the meteorological archives, sourced from snow that fell in the Red Zone. The snowflakes are well preserved in a slide made of Collapse crystals, revealing a unique-gray-green surface when viewed through the slide.
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Elegant Pen
data.introduction:
A beautifully crafted fountain pen, even though it has been used for more than a decade, its surface shows no signs of aging. 
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Furniture Design Sketch
data.introduction:
A worn furniture design manuscript, with the pages curled from frequent handling. Some parts appear to have been blacked out with gunpowder, making them unreadable.
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Common Symbol
data.introduction:
A type of symbol that frequently appears in shelters after WW III. In Bucharest, these symbols can be found on walls everywhere.
Can be used to unlock specific classified briefing in the Elmo Cloud.

data.name: Mom's Locket Box

Legend has it that there is a copper pendant that can dispel darkness. It is magical and beautiful; if someone with an incredibly strong wish opens it, they can see the girl in a white dress living inside.

data.name: Special Mud Biscuits

data.name: Bulwark Stock Bar T1
data.introduction: A Neural Stock Boost Bar specially developed for Bulwark T-Dolls. As a first-generation Stock Bar, the enhancement capability is limited. "Although it's little, it's better than nothing." It can be used to enhance the neural capability of Bulwark T-Dolls.

data.name: Bulwark Stock Bar T2
data.introduction: A Neural Stock Boost Bar specially developed for Bulwark T-Dolls. After improvements, it can already meet the needs of the initial stage. "My requirements are not high; bring me another 100 according to this standard." It can be used to enhance the neural capability of Bulwark T-Dolls.

data.name: Bulwark Stock Bar T3
data.introduction:
A Stock Boost Bar specially developed for Bulwark T-Dolls. The research has made significant progress, greatly increasing the neural capacity. "It needs to reach at least this level to be worth the expansion, right?" 
It can be used to increase the neural capability of Bulwark T-Dolls.

data.name: Bulwark Stock Bar T4
data.introduction: A Neural Stock Boost Bar specially developed for the Bulwark T-Dolls. Even if it is a Stock Bar, it must align with the technical strength of continuous improvement. "Less is more, understand?" It can be used to increase the neural capability of Bulwark T-Dolls.

data.name: Bulwark Stock Bar T5
data.introduction: A Neural Stock Boost Bar specially developed for Bulwark T-Dolls. This new generation of products looks similar to the previous generation, with conservative upgrades - just like some technological products. It can be used to increase the neural capability of Bulwark T-Dolls.

data.name: Bulwark Stock Bar T6
data.introduction: A Stock Boost Bar specially developed for Bulwark T-Dolls. The last generation product before the technology iteration, due to the early leak of information, had dismal sales, but later was proven to be very cost-effective and once again became the mainstream of the market. It can be used for the Neural enhancement of Bulwark T-Dolls.

data.name: Cured Glue
data.introduction: A necessary adhesive for special weapons. Although it's easy to use, it comes at a high price and is a rare item found in Contamination Zones.

data.name: Analysis Blueprint
data.introduction:
A set of analysis blueprints detailing various parameters of weapons, with each component explained in detail. "I really hope this can become the industry standard."
Can be used to enhance weapon proficiency.

data.name: Easy Analysis Blueprints
data.introduction:
Basic weapon analysis blueprints, with a standardized format but with relatively brief content. "There isn't much useful information, but at least the format is clear and easy to understand."
Can be used to enhance weapon proficiency from level 21 to 30.

data.name: Standard Analysis Blueprints
data.introduction:
Standard weapon analysis blueprints, with a clear structure and complete annotations. "I've read every word; at least I'll understand a bit more."
Can be used to enhance weapon proficiency from level 31 to 40.

data.name: Precise Analysis Blueprints
data.introduction:
Detailed weapon analysis blueprints that not only record extensive content but also provide accurate descriptions of specific topics. “With so many details, I'll have to put in some effort to remember them all.”
Can be used to enhance weapon proficiency from level 41 to 50.

data.name: In-Depth Analysis Blueprints
data.introduction:
Comprehensive weapon analysis blueprints that detail the operation of each module and interchangable parts, making it accessible even for beginners. "This is exactly the kind of blueprint I wanted!"
Can be used to enhance weapon proficiency from level 51 to 60.

data.name: Expert Analysis Blueprints
data.introduction:
Professional weapon analysis blueprints written by a weapon expert, featuring highly specialized content. "No wonder it's crafted by a weapon specialist; my understanding of weapons has improved again!"
Can be used to enhance weapon proficiency from level 51 to 60.

A collection device developed by IOP, capable of integrating and analyzing a Doll's preset behaviors. When combined with the Neural Helix, it can unlock certain Exclusive Keys. 
Can be used to activate Evolved Nodes.

data.name: Normal Info Core
data.introduction:
The collection device developed by IOP can integrate and analyze the conventional tactical behavior data of Dolls, and combined with the Neural Helix, it can activate some Exclusive Keys. 
Can be used to activate Evolved Nodes.

data.name: Hyper Info Core
data.introduction: IOP developed a high-performance collection device that integrates and analyzes Dolls' particular tactical behavior data and can be combined with the Neural Helix solution to activate the Universal Key. Can be used to activate Evolved Nodes.
data.description: 技能点的激活材料（该材料当前，可以作为备用）

data.name: Papa-Figo
data.introduction: A high-performance handgun with an ingenious, elegant design. Named after a mythical monster said to devour disobedient children, according to its creator.

data.name: Classified Manuscript
data.introduction: A high-performance SMG, a powerful and unique weapon. When he gave it this name, the designer probably intended it to be a secret weapon.

data.name: Arcana
data.introduction: High-performance sniper rifle with a cold and technological appearance. Does the bullet's trajectory also embody the principles of the universe's operation?

data.name: Guerno
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle capable of easily adapting to various combat scenarios. Named after the Valkyrie Guerno, it likely yearns to be wielded by those of noble character.

data.name: Crowned Jackalope
data.introduction: A high-performance melee weapon, immensely powerful with an artistic design. Battles fought with this weapon would undoubtedly be a spectacle to behold.

data.name: Mjölnir
data.introduction: A high-performance machine gun notable for its exceptional capacity and formidable power. The designer's choice of name suggests a hope that users might wield its power with the aptitude of Thor himself.

data.name: Expeditionary Pigeon
data.introduction: A powerful shotgun with sleek lines and tremendous force. With such power, even timid young pigeons might regain their courage and bravely protect their companions.

data.name: Retired UMP9
data.introduction: A low-cost weapon commonly found in contamination zones. Its stock shows some damage, and numerous welding marks are visible across the gun's frame.

data.name: UMP9
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Lenna. Modified based on her combat preferences. Ensures high shooting accuracy despite the increased rate of fire.

data.name: Löwenjunges
data.introduction: A high-performance submachine gun assigned to Lenna. Its modifications are based on the UMP9. Leva's opinions were also considered during the modification process, and Lenna likes this gun very much.

data.name: Retired KSVK
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Poor maintenance has affected its shooting accuracy, so this gun can only be used in a pinch.

data.name: KSVK
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Dushevnaya. Modified based on her preferences in combat. Features varying degrees of improvement to both penetration and shooting accuracy.

data.name: Eulogistic Verse
data.introduction: A high-performance rifle assigned to Dushevnaya. Based on the KSVK, reducing recoil without compromising power. "It speaks to me in a profound way, perhaps as a heroic verse that continues to shine even after a thousand years," says Dushevnaya.

data.name: Retired Three-Line Rifle M1891
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its style is outdated, but it is still sturdy and functional.

data.name: Three-Line Rifle M1891
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Mosin-Nagant. Modified based on her combat preferences. Its streamlined design facilitates easy maintenance and handling.

data.name: Samosek
data.introduction: A high-performance rifle assigned to Mosin-Nagant. Based on the original Three-line Rifle M1891. While retaining its versatility, its power has been pushed to the limit. When Mosin-Nagant raises the rifle and takes aim at the enemy, is she also examining her own heart?

data.name: Retired W 2000
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its frame has some dents, but it doesn't affect the firing efficiency.

data.name: W 2000
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Makiatto. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features include lighter weight and improved shooting accuracy.

data.name: Bittersweet Caramel
data.introduction: A high-performance rifle assigned to Makiatto. Based on the W 2000. It has undergone countless adjustments to achieve ultimate precision and power. Makiatto wields this weapon to break through all obstacles, infusing her simmering emotions into each bullet.

data.name: Retired Type 97
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Appears worn-out, as if it could break at any moment if not handled with care.

data.name: Type 97
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Jiangyu. Modified based on her combat preferences. The reinforced body structure and significant power boost have made it more robust and potent.

data.name: Leaping Tiger
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Jiangyu, based on the Type 97, is an exceptionally reliable weapon. The sound of bullets leaving the barrel is sharp and lively, reminiscent of rousing drumbeats in a musical piece, making it one of Jiangyu's favorites.

data.name: Retired Stechkin
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. This gun is a bit old and can barely hit the target.

data.name: Stechkin
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Ksenia. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features a lighter frame and improved accuracy.

data.name: Retired Pluma Edge
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. While plain and old-fashioned in appearance, it can still be frequently encountered in the contamination zones.

data.name: Pluma Edge
data.introduction: A melee weapon, highly compatible with Ullrid. It has been modified in accordance with her preferences in combat, and is exceedingly sharp and durable.

data.name: Rectrix
data.introduction: A high-performance melee weapon assigned to Ullrid. Exquisitely forged out of high-quality steel whilst adorned with simple floral decorations, this weapon's appearance appears both keen and swift.

data.name: Retired Model ARM
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Somewhat heavy, but overall still reasonably easy to carry.

data.name: Model ARM
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Littara. Modified based on her combat preferences, making it more suitable for harsh environments and comfortable to use.

data.name: Retired Suomi
data.introduction: A cheap weapon from an underground broker. It is scratched and worn all over its frame, but it doesn't affect the gun's function.

data.name: Suomi
data.introduction: A firearm that is highly compatible with Suomi. It has been modified to suit Suomi's fighting style. Reducing the gun's weight has also increased its durability and firepower.

data.name: Unspoken Calling
data.introduction: A high-performance submachine gun issued to Suomi. Modelled after the Suomi, it is both lighter and more powerful than its original, and it is suitable for various complex combat conditions. With this gun, Suomi will accomplish all the missions given to her.

data.name: Retired PPSh-41
data.introduction: A cheap weapon from an underground broker. The frame is mottled and discolored, but it's still solid and reliable.

data.name: PPSh-41
data.introduction: A firearm that is highly compatible with Papasha. It has been modified to suit Papasha's fighting style. While the material is still the same, its frame is more solid.

data.name: Svarog
data.introduction: A high-performance submachine gun issued to Papasha. Modelled after the PPSh, it is lighter than the original while still retaining its predecessor's firepower and low recoil. Papasha holds it high, showing its glorious light off to all.

data.name: Special Instructions: PPSh-41
data.introduction:
An old-fashioned weapon manual, detailing every component.
Can be used to perform Weapon Adjustment to the submachine gun PPSh-41.

data.name: Special Instructions - Svarog
data.introduction:
A brand-new weapon manual with clear printing and detailed content.
Can be used to perform Weapon Adjustment to the Svarog.

data.name: Retired M1 Super 90
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its performance and appearance are both equally unremarkable.

data.name: M1 Super 90
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Lotta, it has been modified to suit Lotta's fighting style. The power and endurance has been significantly boosted.

data.name: Retired G36K-KSK
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It's really old and worn out, and looks like it's reaching the upper limit of its lifespan.

data.name: G36K-KSK
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Andoris. Modified based on her combat preferences, it features improved firepower and error correction.

data.name: Aglaea
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Andoris. Based on the G36K-KSK. Designed for ease of handling and reliability, it features enhanced firepower, ensuring Andoris can confidently protect those she holds dear.

data.name: Retired Skoda 75
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. There are some problems with the firing mechanism, but one must make do with what they have.

data.name: Skoda 75
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Faye. Modified based on her combat preferences, it is durable, light, and easy to handle.

data.name: Hestia
data.introduction: A high-performance handgun assigned to Faye. Based on the Skoda 75, it is convenient to carry, reliable, precise, and accurate. In Faye's hands, Hestia becomes as fearsome as a true Goddess of Flame.

data.name: Retired Ksvec .45 ACP
data.introduction: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It's about to completely fall apart, but can still be used if you are careful enough.

data.name: Ksvec .45 ACP
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Vector. Modified based on her combat preferences, it is highly maneuverable and stable.

data.name: Banshee's Whisper
data.introduction: A high-performance submachine gun assigned to Vector. Based on the Ksvec .45 ACP, it has been completely overhauled. Pull the trigger, and let death whisper a song into the ears of enemies.

data.name: Retired Sturmgewehr 28
data.introduction: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It shows a high degree of erosion by the elements.

data.name: Sturmgewehr 28
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Belka. Modified based on her combat preferences, it is now even more suited for long-range shooting.

data.name: Sylvan Elf
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Belka. Based on the Sturmgewehr 28, it has been further improved in terms of shooting accuracy, precision and firepower. She bounces around the battlefield like an elf in a forest, pushing back intruders with agility and precision.

data.name: Retired Springfield
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It’s not very stable or reliable, but can still be used, more or less.

data.name: Springfield
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Springfield. Modified based on her combat preferences, it provides increased bullet velocity, hence improving firepower.

data.name: Radiance
data.introduction: A high-performance rifle assigned to Springfield. Based on the Springfield, it has been further improved in terms of carrying convenience and firing speed. Pierce through all adversity, to carve out a brighter future for those you deem important.

data.name: Retired Type 97 Shotgun
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. While it runs the risk of jamming, it can handle the daily demands of protection work.

data.name: Type 97 Shotgun
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Qiuhua. Modified based on her combat preferences. Its recoil has been reduced and its long-range accuracy has been improved.

data.name: Trailblazer
data.introduction: A high-performance shotgun assigned to Qiuhua. Based on the Type 97 Shotgun. Its reliability and stopping power have been maximized. Even the faintest mote of starlight is enough to banish the infinite darkness.

data.name: Retired CS/LS06
data.introduction: A cheap weapon from an underground broker. Its barrel is a little rusty, and its lethality is in question.

data.name: CS/LS06
data.introduction: A firearm that is highly compatible with Zhaohui. It has been modified to suit Zhaohui's fighting style. It's lighter and handier, improving its accuracy on the move.

data.name: Juggernaut
data.introduction: A high-performance submachine gun issued to Zhaohui. Modelled after the CS/LS06, its lethality has been greatly increased, making it a blade of righteousness for a chivalrous warrior. "A man slain with but a step and slash, A journey unending for a thousand miles."

data.name: Retired G11
data.introduction: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It is tattered and worn, but can still be used.

data.name: G11
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Mechty. Modified based on her combat preferences, it has improved rate of fire, precision and accuracy.

data.name: Daydream
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Mechty. Based on the G11, its firepower has been further improved. A gun that complements Mechty's burst-firing nature, it is dedicated to shattering the daydreams of enemies.

data.name: Retired 416
data.introduction: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It looks old, but the damage to it is minimal and it can be used normally.
A firearm that is highly compatible with Klukai. It has been modified to suit Klukai's fighting style, granting it a significant increase in reliability and accuracy.

data.name: Skylla
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle issued to Klukai, modelled after the 416. Its flexibility has been greatly increased, making it suitable for various combat tactics. Its perfect appearance and performance belies its rampant ambition, and its fangs will tear all foes to shreds.
A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It's missing a few parts, but it's still (barely) usable.
A firearm highly compatible with Peri. Modified based on her combat preferences. It's equipped with some parts scavenged from unknown origins, which has slightly improved its rate of fire.

A high-performance SMG assigned to Peri. Based on the Maschinenpistole 5. Its internals have been modified to greatly increase its stopping power. It deceives foes with its attractive appearance and crushes them with absolute power.

data.name: Retired K2
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its surface is covered in carbon streaks and wear, so please be careful when using it.

data.name: K2
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Yoohee. Modified based on her combat preferences. Its stability and ease of carrying have been greatly improved, ensuring firing accuracy on the move.

data.name: Sparkling Centerstage
data.introduction: A high-performance rifle assigned to Yoohee. Based on the K2, its killing power and portability have been maximized. Even the faintest spark can still do its best to light the way forward for the people it cherishes.

data.name: Retired Veska 94
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its iron sights are worn down but it's still usable.

data.name: Veska 94
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Nikketa. Modified based on her combat preferences. Its weight has been reduced, making it lighter and easier to handle on missions.

data.name: Guardian Silverwing
data.introduction: A high-performance rifle assigned to Nikketa. Based on the Veska-94. Its shooting precision has been upgraded, turning it into the ultimate tool for protecting justice. It nips all evil in the bud, so the children can sleep soundly and have sweet dreams.

data.name: Hare
data.introduction: A melee weapon highly compatible with Krolik. Modified based on her combat preferences and painted with a skin that matches Krolik's colors.

data.name: Retired .380 Curva
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Commonly used by bounty hunters in contamination zones. This gun is ancient, but it can still be used with daily maintenance.

data.name: Retired .50 Nemesis
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Used to be military standard issue equipment. The gun frame has many noticeable scars, and it is barely usable.

data.name: Retired OTs-14
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker, with signs of multiple repairs. Its combat effectiveness is problematic and can barely be considered better than nothing.

data.name: .50 Nemesis
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Nemesis. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features further improved firepower and accuracy.

data.name: .380 Curva
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Colphne. Modified based on her combat preferences. The modifications make it practical, compact, and easy to use, while also enhancing its power.

data.name: Heart Seeker
data.introduction: A high-performance shotgun assigned to Vepley. Based on the Vepr-12. Designed to protect the audience in case of unexpected incidents during her performances. However, as a professional idol, Vepley might use this gun to secretly capture the hearts of her fans.

data.name: Retired Vepr-12
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It's been used for too long and is now only barely able to fire.

data.name: Optical Illusion
data.introduction: A high-performance machine gun assigned to Peritya. Based on the Pecheneg-SP. After modifications, its power has been significantly enhanced. Will the one wielding this weapon also vanish like an illusion?

data.name: Vepr-12
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Vepley. Modified based on her combat preferences, making it a "performance prop" more suitable for cute and energetic idols.

data.name: Retired Hare
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its surface shows wear, its luster is dull, and its sharpness is average.

data.name: OTs-14
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Groza. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features improved firepower and burst fire effectiveness while ensuring that it's still easy to carry.

data.name: Retired Pecheneg-SP
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. After some modification it became slightly lighter, suitable for individual use. The gun frame shows obvious signs of damage.

data.name: Pecheneg-SP
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Peritya. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features improved firepower and portability, becoming more potent in Peritya's hands.

data.name: Retired Robinson Modular Rifle
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Although maintained regularly, it has seen many battles and sustained damage, which significantly reduced its performance.

data.name: Robinson Modular Rifle
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Sharkry. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features improved overall balance and enhanced shooting precision.

data.name: Retired Model Alpha
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It can still fire normally, but its frame is in poor condition and only barely usable.

data.name: Model Alpha
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Tololo. Modified based on her combat preferences. improving shooting accuracy and adapting it to various combat environments.

data.name: Planeta
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Tololo. Based on the Model Alpha. Features include lighter frame and higher shooting accuracy. Its lightweight, innovative design combines pragmatic rationality with the romance of exploring the unknown, much like its owner.

data.name: Retired MP7H1
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It power and rate of fire are reduced due to a lack of timely maintenance.

data.name: MP7H1
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Cheeta. Modified based on her combat preferences. Offers substantial firepower despite featuring a small and extremely light frame.

data.name: Retired QBZ-191
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It's covered in scratches, as if it had weathered many storms.

data.name: QBZ-191
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Qiongjiu. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features increased firing stability and accuracy.

data.name: Golden Melody
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Qiongjiu. Based on the QBZ-191. The adjustments ensure its versatility in various environments while enhancing its power and stability. Beneath its steady rhythm lies an unchanged purpose.

data.name: Retired Sportivo Calibro 12
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Severely worn out, it appears close to complete disrepair.

data.name: Sportivo Calibro 12
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Sabrina. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features lighter weight, making it easier to carry and use.

data.name: Mezzaluna
data.introduction: A high-performance shotgun assigned to Sabrina. Based on the Sportivo Calibro 12. Features a unique design that improves stability and makes the gun easier to store and carry while maintaining an intimidating appearance. To avoid frightening others, Sabrina named it after a common kitchen utensil from Italian cuisine.

data.name: Retired Nagant M1895
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its surface is covered in rust, but it can still function after thorough maintenance.

data.name: Nagant M1895
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Nagant. Modified based on her combat preferences. Offers higher initial bullet velocity and improved durability.

data.name: Retired Type 95
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its frame shows numerous repair marks but it still fires normally.

data.name: Type 95
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Daiyan. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features lighter weight and improved stability.

data.name: Heavy Strings
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Daiyan. Based on the Type 95. Combines elegant appearance with destructive power. In Daiyan's hands, this "Heavy Strings" resonates like a deadly musical instrument.

data.name: Retired Sturmgewehr 36
data.introduction: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Poorly maintained, requiring a thorough inspection before use.

data.name: Sturmgewehr 36
data.introduction: A firearm highly compatible with Centaureissi. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features further reduced weight.

data.name: Maid's Rules
data.introduction: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Centaureissi. Based on the Sturmgewehr 36 and crafted with materials of exceptional quality. As precise and refined as its owner. It embodies the wielder's convictions and principles.

data.name: Portrait - Swift Blade
data.introduction:
Krolik appears in her usual outfit, with her iconic bunny ears standing out. 
Unlocked after obtaining Krolik.

data.name: Portrait - Galaxy Interpretation
data.introduction:
Nemesis appears in her usual attire. What was she thinking when she left this illustration? 
Unlocked after obtaining Nemesis.

data.name: Portrait - Sweetheart Rescue
data.introduction:
Colphne, who usually appears in her everyday outfit, is always remembered with a smile, rarely expressionless like this. 
Unlocked after obtaining Colphne.

data.name: Portrait - Energetic Focus
data.introduction:
Vepley appears in her usual attire. Her quiet demeanor is a bit unsettling. 
Unlocked after obtaining Vepley.

data.name: Portrait - Blade's Aegis
data.introduction:
Groza appears in everyday clothing, which makes people feel at ease and reassured.
Unlocked after obtaining Groza.

data.name: Portrait - Dual Hunter
data.introduction:
Peritya appears in everyday clothing. Don't let your guard down just because of her gentle and lazy appearance. 
Unlocked after obtaining Peritya.

data.name: Portrait - Radiance Noctune
data.introduction:
Sharkry appears in her usual attire. Facing this cute face, no matter what she asks, you will gladly agree, right? 
Unlocked after obtaining Sharkry.

data.name: Portrait - Whimsical Military Uniform
data.introduction: Cheeta appears in everyday clothes with a focused look in her eyes. What beautiful ideas does she have? Unlocked after obtaining Cheeta.

data.name: Portrait - Grey Meteor
data.introduction: Tololo, appearing in regular attire, has a somewhat absent-minded expression, likely browsing the astronomical images stored in her neural mind. Unlocked after obtaining Tololo.

data.name: Portrait - Winter Woods Walk
data.introduction: Nagant, appearing in everyday clothes, may be small, but she's a veteran. Unlocked after obtaining Nagant.

data.name: Portrait - Celestial Grace
data.introduction: Qiongjiu, wearing everyday clothes, sports a unique jade bead on her head. Unlocked after obtaining Qiongjiu.

data.name: Icon: Flawless Hospitality
data.introduction:
Centaureissi in her usual outfit. When you see this, you can practically smell the fragrance of black tea. 
Unlocked after obtaining Centaureissi.

data.name: Portrait - Charming Kitchen Chef
data.introduction: Sabrina, in her usual outfit, has lively, chubby cheeks. Unlocked after obtaining Sabrina.

data.name: Portrait - Smoke Seeking
data.introduction: Daiyan, appearing in everyday clothing, has a gentle expression and elegant manners. Unlocked after obtaining Daiyan.

data.name: Avatar - Amidst Wings of Gray
data.introduction:
An auspicious beast of ceremony, discarded in the silent wind and dust. Once, people made wishes to it for the well-being of their families.
Unlocked via completion of Amidst Wings of Gray story stages.

data.name: Portrait - Hard at Work
data.introduction:
Mosin-Nagant in her usual outfit, with a look that shows she's motivated to work on the Elmo. 
Unlocked after obtaining Mosin-Nagant.

data.name: Portrait - New Job Celebration
data.introduction:
Ksenia in her usual outfit, captured in this portrait with an especially serious expression. 
Unlocked after obtaining Ksenia.

data.name: Portrait - Today's Mail
data.introduction:
Littara in her usual outfit. Although she may seem expressionless in her portrait, but in reality, she is quite nervous inside. 
Unlocked after obtaining Littara.

data.name: Codename "Zucchero"
data.introduction:
A return gift from Zucchero, and also a memento.
Unlocked after completing the Zucchero Cafe Story Mode campaign.

data.name: Icon: Swift Messenger
data.introduction:
Lenna appears in her usual attire. Below her confident smile is the determination to protect her family. :3
Unlocked after obtaining Lenna.

data.name: Icon: Pattering Rain
data.introduction:
Jiangyu appears in her usual attire. Her lively smile will surely banish your bad mood.
Unlocked after obtaining Jiangyu.

data.name: Portrait - Fatal Disguise
data.introduction:
Makiatto appears in her usual attire. She has made up her mind to protect that important person herself. 
Unlocked after obtaining Makiatto.

data.name: Icon: Intertwined Assault
data.introduction:
We face different difficulties in different places. Each point of light ultimately culminates into a dazzling radiance, lighting the way ahead. 
Unlocked after clearing all normal stages of Intertwined Assault.

data.name: Icon: Best Actress
data.introduction:
A stirring story is currently playing out on a grand stage.
Unlocked after clearing all normal stages of Vestigial Display

data.name: Icon: Jiangyu's Roots
data.introduction:
Pass on your heritage and defend it. When danger is at hand, protect those who are precious to you.
Unlocked by claiming the final reward from Vestigial Display - Special Commission

data.name: Portrait - Sweet Little Bear
data.introduction:
Will hiding inside a fluffy mascot outfit make a certain Doll who can't speak her mind a little more honest?
Unlocked by completing Rhapsody Quartet story stages.

data.name: Portrait - Crazy Mech Soldier
data.introduction:
There are no difficult tasks, only the brave Small Beepy! 
Unlocked by collecting the final reward of the Rhapsody Quartet - Rhapsody Commission.

data.name: Portrait - Summer Pitcher
data.introduction: With a perfect pitch, Nagant showcases the authority of a senior. Unlocked after obtaining Nagant's Outfit - Summer Pitcher.

data.name: Portrait - Krolik's Training Outfit
data.introduction:
Dressed in her training uniform, Krolik appeares even more formidable than when she's wearing her bunny ears. 
Unlocked after obtaining Krolik's Combat Suit - Training Outfit.

data.name: Portrait - Nemesis' Training Outfit
data.introduction: Nemesis in Nemesis' Training Suit can hit the target silently without the cover of the cloak. Unlock after obtaining Nemesis' Combat Suit - Nemesis' Training Outfit.

data.name: Portrait - Colphne's Training Outfit
data.introduction: Colphne, wearing her training suit, exhibits an unusual, eye-catching agility. Unlock after obtaining Colphne's Combat Suit - Colphne's Training Outfit.

data.name: Portrait - Groza's Training Outfit
data.introduction: Groza in training clothes. Her equipment is simplified, but her strength remains the same. Unlock after obtaining Groza's Combat Suit - Groza's Training Outfit.

data.name: Portrait - Prancing Bunny
data.introduction:
Krolik, wearing a light and simple outfit, stands out in the group. 
Unlocked after obtaining Krolik's Outfit - Prancing Bunny.

data.name: Portrait - Dawn of Battle
data.introduction:
Dawn is coming, and victory is clear in Groza's eyes. 
Unlocked after obtaining Groza's Combat Suit - Dawn of Battle.

data.name: Portrait - Serene Dark River
data.introduction: The dark black outfit allows her to blend into the night quietly. Unlock after obtaining Nemesis' Combat Suit - Serene Dark River.

data.name: Portrait - Wandering Star Trail
data.introduction:
An unusual outfit that seems to hints at Nemesis' mysterious past. 
Unlocked after obtaining Nemesis' Combat Suit - Wandering Star Trail.

data.name: Portrait - Sparkling Wish
data.introduction:
"Make all the audience happy..." With this dream in mind, the idol stands on the stage. 
Unlocked after obtaining Vepley's Combat Suit - Sparkling Wish.

data.name: Portrait - Sangria Succulent
data.introduction:
On a lonely night, Groza, dressed in gorgeous clothes, awaits you. 
Unlocked after obtaining Groza's Outfit - Sangria Succulent.

data.name: Portrait - Narcissus
data.introduction:
Clad in clothes as pure as jade, with the sound of the zither echoing exquisitely, a heart of purity is devoted to only one person.
Unlocked after obtaining Daiyan's Outfit - Narcissus.

data.name: Icon: Vitality Magic
data.introduction:
With flowers, ribbons and a cute pair of twintails, the lively magical girl Lenna makes her grand debut!
Unlocked after obtaining Lenna's "Vitality Magic" outfit.

data.name: Portrait - Summer Echo
data.introduction:
Those aren't rolling waves, but ripples of an azure skirt.
Unlocked after obtaining Vepley's outfit - Summer Echo.

data.name: Portrait - Ballroom Interlude
data.introduction:
The elegantly dressed performer—can she still maintain her composure upon noticing you?
Unlocked after obtaining Makiatto's Outfit - Ballroom Interlude.

data.name: Portrait - Celestial River At Dusk
data.introduction:
She weaves the twinkling starlight into a radiant garment, eager to enjoy the seaside night with you.
Unlocked after obtaining Tololo's outfit Celestial River At Dusk.

data.name: Portrait - Sparkling Ocean
data.introduction:
Her clothes flutter in the sea breeze, just like Suomi's relaxed mood. 
Unlocked after obtaining Suomi's Outfit - Sparkling Ocean.

data.name: Portrait - Strong Will
data.introduction:
An unyielding will is embodied in the arrow feathers.
Unlocked by completing Sojourners of the Glass Island - Part I.

data.name: Portrait - Who is the King
data.introduction:
Once you become king, you can issue commands with royal authority!
Unlocked by completing Sojourners of the Glass Island Part II.

data.name: Icon: White Cosmos
data.introduction:
Dushevnaya appears in her usual attire. Is she recalling some precious moment from the past under that earnest expression of hers?
Unlocked after obtaining Dushevnaya.

data.name: Portrait - Guiding Thornlight
data.introduction:
Ullrid appears in her usual attire. Her eyes are determined, like she's gazing into the distance.
 Unlocked after obtaining Ullrid.

data.name: Portrait - Snow Bright
data.introduction:
Suomi in her typical attire, appearing both soft and fluffy as she bravely carries out her mission. 
Unlocked after obtaining Suomi.

data.name: Icon: Forthright Safeguard
data.introduction:
Papasha in her usual outfit. With her hat on and wrench in hand, she's ready to help everyone out.
Unlocked after obtaining Papasha.

data.name: Portrait - Spiritual Grass
data.introduction:
Lotta in her usual outfit. She seems worried about something.
Unlocked after obtaining Lotta.

data.name: Portrait - Leisurely Patroller
data.introduction:
Andoris in her usual outfit. She has a friendly and approachable smile. Smile more, for many things are not truly that big of a deal.
Unlocked after obtaining Andoris.

data.name: Portrait - Red Hot Bell Pepper
data.introduction:
Faye in her usual outfit. She looks really unapproachable, but don't worry. She's simply deep in thought about what her next words should be.
Unlocked after obtaining Faye.

data.name: Portrait - Concealment Gear
data.introduction:
Vector in her usual outfit. She has gotten a little more "leader-like" as time passes.
Unlocked after obtaining Vector.

data.name: Portrait - Leaping Signal
data.introduction:
Belka in her usual outfit. Her bright, lively colors serve as a silent warning to enemies.
Unlocked after obtaining Belka.

data.name: Portrait - Clean Military Uniform
data.introduction:
Springfield in her usual outfit. She still maintains an attire suited for the battlefield, but who is to say that the Zucchero Café and the world in the shadows behind it are not just another battlefield?
Unlocked after obtaining Springfield.

data.name: Portrait - S-Grade Cuisine Hunter
data.introduction:
Qiuhua appears in her usual attire. Fine cuisine is her specialty, whether in terms of making it or eating it. 
Unlocked after obtaining Qiuhua.

data.name: Icon: Drifting Cloud
data.introduction:
Zhaohui appears in her usual attire. Though she always wears a cold expression, she is surprisingly eager lend a hand. 
Unlocked after obtaining Zhaohui.

data.name: Portrait - Dreamland Wars
data.introduction:
Mechty in her usual outfit. She seems calm, but she yawned the next second.
Unlocked after obtaining Mechty.

data.name: Icon: Blazing Star
data.introduction:
Klukai in her usual outfit. As dazzling as ever, showing off her heroic poise.
Unlocked after obtaining Klukai.

data.name: Icon: Hero's Radar
data.introduction:
This steel-bodied hero will aid those in difficulty today.
Unlocked by obtaining the final category of reward in Halting Station - Encampment Commision.

data.name: Icon: Maiden's Wish
data.introduction:
A girl who helps others fulfil their wishes might secretly make a wish of her own.
Unlock by completing all Halting Encampment story stages.

data.name: Portrait - Strawberry Zabaione
data.introduction:
Berry-colored hair accessories and delicious food, together with the fiery sunset, make up Sabrina's summer beach memories.
Unlocks after obtaining Sabrina's outfit - Strawberry Zabaione.

data.name: Icon: Superspeed Chequer
data.introduction:
The checkered flag symbolizes the finish line and victory. Tighten your belt, stretch your muscles. Zhaohui is ready for the next wild race. 
Unlocked after obtaining Zhaohui's "Superspeed Chequer" outfit.

data.name: Icon: Speed Star
data.introduction:
A racing silver flash tears through the darkness. As the scenery fades into a blur, the sole constant is the silver rider's keen gaze.
Unlocked after obtaining Klukai's outfit - Speed Star.

data.name: Portrait - Stars Beyond
data.introduction:
In the vast starry sky, you're the Polaris guiding her gaze.
A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

data.name: Portrait - Frost Upon Ink
data.introduction:
A pure heart, given to my lord.
A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

Despite her cool exterior, she will give her all and show her smile to you and you alone.
A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

data.introduction:
No matter how difficult the skill, she'd learn it just to help you. 
A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

The wandering wind finally comes to rest here.

Unlocked after obtaining Peri.

Yoohee appears in her usual attire. Her outfit combines multiple elements from modern fashion, and on the whole it comes off as flexible and adaptable
Unlocked after obtaining Yoohee.

Nikketa in her usual outfit. Her immaculate uniform showcases her determination to see justice done. 
Unlocked after obtaining Nikketa.

Unlocked by acquiring Cheeta's Outfit - Racecourse Sparks

The most important person in your life deserves your protection 24 hours a day.

An idol's most perfect song will always be sung for the most important fan.

A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

data.introduction:
Love is being conveyed through a Guzheng's song, the meaning known only to the couple.
A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

data.introduction:
She smiles gently because of your existence.
A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.

Each meal made for you is filled with her sweet feelings.
A heartfelt return gift from your Doll, obtained after forming a Covenant.
